sql:
SELECT DISTINCT s.name
FROM species s
JOIN observations o ON s.species_id = o.species_id;

SELECT *
FROM users
WHERE status = 'Active' AND user_id IN (
    SELECT created_by
    FROM notes
);

external_knowledge:
- 'enthusiasts' refers to the users who made observations; 
- 'contributions' here means the number of observations made by each user;
- 'most active' refers to users with the highest number of observations.
